views.text: Driving on the Uber App is limited to no more than 12 hours at a time. If you’re offline, or stopped between trips, the time is not counted toward the 12-hour limit.
After being offline for 6 hours, you’ll be able to go back online to receive new Uber trips.
Taking time to rest throughout the day is important to your health and safety, but it doesn't count toward the required 6 hours offline.
